--TEST--
Installing a package with a not existing feature should fail
--COMPOSER--
{
    "repositories": [
        {
            "type": "package",
            "package": [
                { "name": "a/a", "version": "1.0.0", "features": { "b": { "require": { "b/b": "1.0.0" } } } },
                { "name": "b/b", "version": "1.0.0" }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "require": {
        "a/a": "1.0.0"
    },
    "require-features": {
        "a/a": ["unknown"]
    }
}
--RUN--
update
--EXPECT-EXIT-CODE--
2

--EXPECT-OUTPUT--
Loading composer repositories with package information
Updating dependencies
Your requirements could not be resolved to an installable set of packages.

  Problem 1
    - Root composer.json requires a/a 1.0.0 -> satisfiable by a/a[1.0.0].
    - Root composer.json requires feature "unknown" for a/a -> could not be found.

Potential causes:
 - A typo in the package name
 - The package is not available in a stable-enough version according to your minimum-stability setting
   see <https://getcomposer.org/doc/04-schema.md#minimum-stability> for more details.
 - It's a private package and you forgot to add a custom repository to find it

Read <https://getcomposer.org/doc/articles/troubleshooting.md> for further common problems.

--EXPECT--
